"title": "6126: condemnation, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6126: condemnation, human",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The passing of judgment on others. This is valid when authorised by God, but otherwise it is frequently partial, godless and self-protecting, and therefore unacceptable.</p>\n<h2>Condemnation and the legal process: impartial judgment demanded</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:6-Exod23:8\">EXO 23:6–23:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:15-Deut1:17\">DEU 1:15–1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:2-Deut17:7\">DEU 17:2–17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:15\">DEU 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:4-2Chr19:7\">2CH 19:4–19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:15\">PRO 17:15</a></p>\n<h2>The perversity and injustice of human condemnation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:1-Rom2:5\">ROM 2:1–2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:1-2Sam12:10\">2SA 12:1–12:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:1-Dan6:16\">DAN 6:1–6:16</a></p>\n<h2>People's false condemnation of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:27-Acts13:28\">ACT 13:27–13:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:59-Matt26:63\">MAT 26:59–26:63</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:55-Mark14:61\">MRK 14:55–14:61</a></p>\n<h2>NT warnings against judgment and condemnation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:1-Matt7:5\">MAT 7:1–7:5</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:37-Luke6:38\">LUK 6:37–6:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:41-Luke6:42\">LUK 6:41–6:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3-John8:11\">JHN 8:3–8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1-Rom14:4\">ROM 14:1–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:9-Rom14:13\">ROM 14:9–14:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's protection of his people from false condemnation</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:7-Isa50:9\">ISA 50:7–50:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:31-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:31–8:39</a></p>",
